  "text": "The log retention policy in Kafka is enforced across these files: (1) TopicConfig.java defines the RETENTION_MS_CONFIG and RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG constants. (2) ServerLogConfigs.java defines the broker-level LOG_RETENTION_TIME_MILLIS_CONFIG and LOG_RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG with defaults and documentation. (3) ServerTopicConfigSynonyms.java maps topic-level retention configs to their broker-level log.* prefixed synonyms. (4) LogConfig.java holds the parsed retentionMs/retentionSize fields and contains all validation logic (validateValues, validateRemoteStorageRetentionSize, validateRemoteStorageRetentionTime, validateRetentionConfigsWhenRemoteCopyDisabled, and the top-level validate method). (5) UnifiedLog.java is the core enforcement point \u2014 deleteOldSegments() orchestrates retention by calling deleteRetentionMsBreachedSegments() for time-based retention and deleteRetentionSizeBreachedSegments() for size-based retention, plus deleteLogStartOffsetBreachedSegments(). It also provides localRetentionMs/localRetentionSize helper methods for tiered storage. (6) LogCleaner.java runs the retention cleanup loop, fetching deletableLogs from LogCleanerManager and calling deleteOldSegments() on each. (7) LogCleanerManager.java identifies which logs are eligible for deletion via its deletableLogs() method.",
